<!--
    Faroese (Føroyskt) — fo
    Script : Latin (+ á í ó ú ý æ ø); LTR.
    Approx.: ~75 000 speakers (Faroe Islands + diaspora).
    Register: Standard Faroese (Faroese Language Committee norms).
    Notes  : Faroese is the official language of the Faroe Islands, an autonomous
             territory of Denmark.  It has four cases and grammatical gender
             (masculine, feminine, neuter).  "Binge drinking" → óhóvliga
             drakking / drukkin — the neutral clinical term óhóvliga drakking
             is preferred in health contexts.
    Source : Translated from values-de/strings.xml (German source of truth).
-->
